675
01:06:52,023 --> 01:06:54,014
Hey!

676
01:07:01,828 --> 01:07:05,821
-Can you help me with my bag? -No problem.

677
01:07:15,836 --> 01:07:18,031
What are you doing?

678
01:07:36,649 --> 01:07:38,549
Slow down!

679
01:07:58,861 --> 01:08:02,228
The toilets will be open in five minutes.

680
01:08:20,274 --> 01:08:24,836
[Grunting, Groaning]

681
01:08:28,078 --> 01:08:30,171
Don't even think about it!

682
01:08:31,481 --> 01:08:34,973
[Wrist Snaps, Groaning Continues]

683
01:08:35,049 --> 01:08:38,485
Next time you pick that lock don't leave them scratch marks.

684
01:08:38,584 --> 01:08:41,781
Bastard! [Grunts]

685
01:09:03,165 --> 01:09:05,156
Harold.

686
01:09:05,199 --> 01:09:07,497
-Hey, put that away. -What?

687
01:09:07,567 --> 01:09:10,161
-Give me some pain pills. -Here.

688
01:09:12,003 --> 01:09:14,301
-Harold, these... these ones? -Yes.

689
01:09:20,609 --> 01:09:25,569
So... Rudy, why are we going to El Paso?

690
01:09:25,612 --> 01:09:28,410
[Coughs] I gotta look up some old friends.

691
01:09:28,479 --> 01:09:30,777
-Oh. -I gotta pick up a suitcase.

692
01:09:30,814 --> 01:09:33,874
Then I'm gonna head south of the border. Real far south.

693
01:09:33,916 --> 01:09:36,908
Oh, that sounds great.

694
01:09:37,018 --> 01:09:40,283
I love to travel, but Harold never wants to go anywhere.

695
01:09:40,320 --> 01:09:44,086
-That's not true. -It's true. We never go anywhere.

696
01:09:44,122 --> 01:09:47,285
[Rudy] He'd rather stay home and play with all of his little critters.

697
01:09:47,324 --> 01:09:49,884
Isn't that right, Harold? [Chuckles]

698
01:09:49,925 --> 01:09:52,894
[Rudy] You poor old bugger.

699
01:10:12,639 --> 01:10:15,437
[Laughs]

700
01:10:45,191 --> 01:10:47,591
I got us a car that I hot-wired.

701
01:10:47,692 --> 01:10:50,092
-[Chuckles] -Come on, let's go.

702
01:10:52,395 --> 01:10:54,488
-Bye. -Bye-bye.

703
01:11:04,202 --> 01:11:08,298
Here, Harold, have some chicken. Harold.

704
01:11:08,404 --> 01:11:12,500
No, no. Look, I gotta pull over. I gotta pee.

705
01:11:12,606 --> 01:11:14,506
[Meows]

706
01:11:17,809 --> 01:11:20,778
-Have some fries. -Rudy!

707
01:11:20,811 --> 01:11:24,611
-Here, Harold, have some fries. -[Sighs]

708
01:11:24,680 --> 01:11:27,706
Have some chicken. Here's your chicken.

709
01:11:29,016 --> 01:11:30,984
Hey, some chicken.

710
01:11:31,018 --> 01:11:33,578
Rudy. Goddamn it! What'd you do that for?

711
01:11:33,619 --> 01:11:36,884
You know why I did that? 'Cause it makes me feel good.

712
01:11:36,920 --> 01:11:39,184
-Have some fries. -No, you have a fry.

713
01:11:39,222 --> 01:11:43,420
-Hey! Have some fries, Harold. Hey! -Have a biscuit, Rudy.

714
01:11:43,491 --> 01:11:47,291
-Hey, have some more fries. -Hey, have some chicken.

715
01:11:47,327 --> 01:11:50,296
-[Chuckling] Chicken. -You have some chicken.

716
01:11:50,328 --> 01:11:53,126
-Have some bean sprouts. -[Laughing]

717
01:11:53,230 --> 01:11:56,532
-Hey, stop it! -Fran, get back here!

718
01:11:56,532 --> 01:12:00,525
-You're such a pig! -I've gotta pull over. I've gotta pee!

719
01:12:00,834 --> 01:12:03,701
Oh, I guess we should stop, 'cause Harold has to pee.

720
01:12:03,736 --> 01:12:06,398
Get back in the front.

721
01:12:06,438 --> 01:12:09,635
Get back up there with Harold! Get up there!

722
01:12:13,542 --> 01:12:19,344
I don't want to play... this game... anymore!

723
01:12:19,412 --> 01:12:21,505
You pee in your pants.

724
01:12:28,051 --> 01:12:30,645
[Exhales]

725
01:13:12,576 --> 01:13:15,340
Looks like this guy's a real pro.

726
01:13:17,179 --> 01:13:19,147
Where'd you get this?

727
01:13:19,180 --> 01:13:23,378
It was a gift. I told you, the guy gave it to me.

728
01:13:25,249 --> 01:13:27,547
Yeah, that's him.

729
01:13:30,086 --> 01:13:31,986
Carter McCoy.

730
01:13:32,087 --> 01:13:35,682
