750
01:14:44,529 --> 01:14:48,431
Carter McCoy, also known as Doc McCoy, is wanted...

751
01:14:48,464 --> 01:14:52,560
-in an armed robbery at the Phoenix Dog Track. -Doc.

752
01:14:52,633 --> 01:14:54,869
He is also wanted in connection with a hijacking...

753
01:14:54,869 --> 01:14:58,236
and firebombing of a tanker truck in the track parking lot.

754
01:14:58,337 --> 01:15:01,670
McCoy is an expert safe-cracker. His criminal record indicates...

755
01:15:02,072 --> 01:15:04,939
numerous other well-planned thefts.

756
01:15:04,974 --> 01:15:08,774
He is considered by authorities as the probable mastermind behind the heist...

757
01:15:08,843 --> 01:15:12,176
and should be considered well-armed and extremely dangerous.

758
01:15:12,278 --> 01:15:15,145
-Dad, that's the guy there on TV. -What?

759
01:15:15,180 --> 01:15:18,343
...and immediately contact law enforcement officials.

760
01:15:18,382 --> 01:15:21,579
Here we go, Mel. I think she's gonna like that.

761
01:15:21,650 --> 01:15:24,175
-Say hello to Alice for me, will ya? -Thank you.

762
01:15:25,886 --> 01:15:30,084
-Yes, sir. What can we do for you today? -Let's see.

763
01:15:30,189 --> 01:15:33,090
I'll take that black 12-gauge pump gun.

764
01:15:33,157 --> 01:15:35,887
Ah, the Minelli. That's a good choice.

765
01:15:35,992 --> 01:15:38,392
This is a very powerful weapon here, sir.

766
01:15:38,460 --> 01:15:43,397
My brother-in-law uses this very gun to hunt ducks, if you can believe that.

767
01:15:43,463 --> 01:15:45,795
You hit a duck with one of these suckers,

768
01:15:45,864 --> 01:15:48,492
and you're not gonna have many pieces left to eat. [Chuckles]

769
01:15:48,566 --> 01:15:51,301
That's a good weapon, though. What else can I get for you?

770
01:15:51,301 --> 01:15:55,067
-Four boxes of double-aught buck. -Double-aught buck.

771
01:15:55,370 --> 01:15:58,066
Four of 'em. Here we go.

772
01:15:58,105 --> 01:16:01,973
That sounds like a huntin' trip I'd like to be on, I'll tell ya.

773
01:16:02,007 --> 01:16:04,498
These babies'll knock down a wall, if ya need it.

774
01:16:04,575 --> 01:16:06,566
Four boxes of.45 auto shells.

775
01:16:06,609 --> 01:16:10,409
.45 auto shells. Where'd I put those? There they are.

776
01:16:21,718 --> 01:16:25,085
[Car Doors Opening]

777
01:16:25,120 --> 01:16:27,714
Okay, all we need now is a little bit of identification.

778
01:16:27,821 --> 01:16:31,222
And we're gonna have to fill this out for Uncle Sam. One through eight.

779
01:16:31,291 --> 01:16:34,926
Don't forget question C: "Are you a fugitive from justice?"

780
01:16:34,926 --> 01:16:38,293
Don't worry about that. We ask everybody to do that.

781
01:16:43,031 --> 01:16:45,932
I got a dandy here for you. Right here.

782
01:16:46,033 --> 01:16:48,695
-Wrap the shotgun. -[Sighs]

783
01:16:48,733 --> 01:16:51,395
Wrap the shotgun.

784
01:16:51,435 --> 01:16:55,496
40-23, I need a 10-28, please, on an Arizona plate:

785
01:16:55,538 --> 01:16:58,336
Sam-Paul-Queen, four-eight-five.

786
01:16:58,406 --> 01:17:01,842
This will be on a 1987 metallic-blue Camaro.

787
01:17:04,043 --> 01:17:06,534
Look, are you sure you want to do this?

788
01:17:06,611 --> 01:17:11,048
-I want you to shut up, lie down and take a nap. -All right, all right.

789
01:17:11,113 --> 01:17:14,549
[Panting] I know the drill. Count to 100, right?

790
01:17:14,648 --> 01:17:18,948
[Panting Continues] One, two, three,

791
01:17:19,052 --> 01:17:21,612
four, five...

792
01:17:21,653 --> 01:17:25,350
I'm gettin' out of this business. Six...

793
01:17:25,655 --> 01:17:28,021
Keep the change.

794
01:17:30,058 --> 01:17:32,526
Excuse me, are you for hire?

795
01:17:32,559 --> 01:17:35,221
Shift's over. Sorry, lady.

796
01:17:36,561 --> 01:17:38,529
Sorry.

797
01:17:41,831 --> 01:17:44,265
What are you doin'? I said my shift's over.

798
01:17:44,333 --> 01:17:47,962
-You'll have to get another... -We're heading east, pal. Straight out of town.

799
01:17:52,171 --> 01:17:56,608
2-79, car 2-79, come in. Can you do another pickup?

800
01:17:56,707 --> 01:18:00,108
-That's you. Answer it. -What do you want me to say?

801
01:18:00,141 --> 01:18:04,077
-Tell him you got a fare. -The dispatcher ain't gonna fall for that.

802
01:18:04,111 --> 01:18:07,103
She's gonna know the cab's been hijacked, and we're on Third...

803
01:18:07,179 --> 01:18:09,480
He's got the radio on, telling 'em where we are.

804
01:18:09,480 --> 01:18:12,813
-You make a right turn here, or I'm gonna put one in you. -Okay.

805
01:18:20,920 --> 01:18:22,979
[Groaning]

806
01:18:23,022 --> 01:18:27,118
-[Doc] Get out of there, now! -Let's go!

807
01:18:27,224 --> 01:18:29,988
-[Grunts] -[Siren Wailing]

808
01:18:33,794 --> 01:18:35,728
Let's go!

809
01:18:35,795 --> 01:18:38,195
Doc, come on!

810
01:18:40,298 --> 01:18:43,529
Go! Go!

811
01:18:45,234 --> 01:18:48,032
Get in!

812
01:18:49,737 --> 01:18:52,831
[Siren Continues]

813
01:18:55,507 --> 01:18:59,238
-[Grunts] -[Car Horns Honking]

814
01:18:59,342 --> 01:19:02,607
[Tires Screeching]

815
01:19:02,645 --> 01:19:05,512
[Policeman] Fuck! Stay with him!

816
01:19:05,546 --> 01:19:09,346
[Gunshots Continue]

817
01:19:09,415 --> 01:19:12,646
-[Siren Continues] -Keep it steady.

818
01:19:17,353 --> 01:19:19,218
[Carol] On the right!

819
01:19:27,759 --> 01:19:30,455
-On your right, on your right! -[Horn Honking]

820
01:19:34,929 --> 01:19:38,023
[Horns Honking, Tires Screeching]

821
01:19:47,070 --> 01:19:49,231
[Grunts]

822
01:19:55,875 --> 01:19:57,968
[Gunshot]

823
01:19:58,043 --> 01:20:00,170
-[Horn Honking] -Whoa!

824
01:20:01,578 --> 01:20:03,546
Hang on, Doc!

825
01:20:03,579 --> 01:20:06,571
-[Sirens Wailing] -Shit. [Screaming]

826
01:20:06,648 --> 01:20:09,640
[Sirens Wailing]

827
01:20:13,285 --> 01:20:15,480
[Doc] Keep going, keep going!

828
01:20:21,390 --> 01:20:25,258
Negative. We're blocked in the underground parking area.

829
01:20:56,911 --> 01:20:59,675
-We're gonna jump in this thing. -No way.

830
01:20:59,712 --> 01:21:02,374
-Doc, we gotta keep moving. -[Siren Wailing]

831
01:21:02,413 --> 01:21:05,007
[Siren Continues]

832
01:21:07,383 --> 01:21:09,613
Oh, shit, Doc!

833
01:21:09,684 --> 01:21:12,312
[Siren Growing Louder]

834
01:21:17,489 --> 01:21:21,220
[Siren Growing Fainter]

835
01:21:27,994 --> 01:21:31,020
-[Truck Engine Running] -[Thudding Noise]

836
01:21:41,536 --> 01:21:43,470
Shit!

837
01:21:45,739 --> 01:21:49,573
-What? -The cops are out there. We're goin' in the truck.

838
01:22:04,783 --> 01:22:06,944
[Screams]

839
01:22:08,885 --> 01:22:11,877
-[Screaming] God! -Stay back!

840
01:22:11,987 --> 01:22:16,083
-Doc! No! [Screams] -Get back!

841
01:22:16,189 --> 01:22:19,352
Get back! All the way to the back.

842
01:22:26,995 --> 01:22:29,657
-Whoooaah! -[Screams] Oh, God!

843
01:22:34,700 --> 01:22:38,796
[Man On TV] What are you lookin' out the window for?

844
01:22:38,902 --> 01:22:41,769
Somebody else comin' after me?

845
01:22:44,172 --> 01:22:47,164
-[Fran Laughing] -[Growling]

846
01:22:50,410 --> 01:22:52,310
Kitty.

847
01:22:54,111 --> 01:22:57,103
Look, Rudy, he likes it.

848
01:22:57,213 --> 01:22:59,773
-Give me that. -Rudy!

849
01:23:01,716 --> 01:23:04,583
Hey, Harold, come out of the bathroom.

850
01:23:06,886 --> 01:23:10,982
Harold, come on out. My shoulder hurts.

851
01:23:11,021 --> 01:23:12,989
Harold.

852
01:23:21,327 --> 01:23:23,420
-[Kitty Meows] -Rudy!

853
01:23:29,732 --> 01:23:32,132
What are you doin' in there?

854
01:23:45,140 --> 01:23:47,040
[Meows]

855
01:23:48,544 --> 01:23:51,312
-[Zipper Unzips] -[Meows]

856
01:23:51,312 --> 01:23:56,215
-[Urinating] -Hey, Fran, I think it's time to check out.

857
01:24:18,260 --> 01:24:22,356
[Screaming]

858
01:24:28,667 --> 01:24:31,067
Oh!

859
01:24:31,135 --> 01:24:33,831
[Grunts]

860
01:24:38,573 --> 01:24:41,474
[Panting] You okay?

861
01:24:43,476 --> 01:24:45,467
I think so. I don't know.

862
01:24:59,885 --> 01:25:03,377
Don't scratch yourself around here. You're gonna get an infection.

863
01:25:15,293 --> 01:25:17,784
-I wanna tell you something. -I don't wanna hear it.

864
01:25:17,862 --> 01:25:19,887
Hey, this is hard for me.

865
01:25:19,963 --> 01:25:23,455
When we get to El Paso, I think I should take off.

866
01:25:31,936 --> 01:25:34,336
Hey, listen to me.

867
01:25:38,541 --> 01:25:41,442
I want you to stick with me.

868
01:25:46,044 --> 01:25:48,444
No more about Benyon.

869
01:25:50,547 --> 01:25:53,948
You and me. What do you say?

870
01:26:00,753 --> 01:26:04,655
[Sighing] Can't get much worse than this, Doc.

871
01:26:04,755 --> 01:26:07,553
I don't see how it could.

872
01:26:13,160 --> 01:26:15,424
Got us a car.

873
01:26:15,462 --> 01:26:18,625
Got a couple of tires. We're in business.

874
01:26:24,333 --> 01:26:26,267
Yep.

875
01:26:26,334 --> 01:26:30,065
Hey, we get to Mexico, we're gonna have a new life. Right?

876
01:26:30,170 --> 01:26:32,365
That's all I want.

877
01:26:47,880 --> 01:26:51,941
[Dialing Touch Tone Phone]

878
01:26:51,983 --> 01:26:55,385
-[Telephone Rings] -Yeah, Tom here.

879
01:26:55,385 --> 01:26:58,650
Tell Jim Deer Rudy and some girl just drove up.

880
01:26:58,987 --> 01:27:02,286
Looks like they're headin' into the hotel.

881
01:27:05,591 --> 01:27:07,491
[Meows]

882
01:27:07,592 --> 01:27:11,084
[Man] Howdy, folks. Welcome to the rustic Border Hotel.

883
01:27:11,160 --> 01:27:15,896
-You must be Gollie. -[Laughing] By golly, I am Gollie.

884
01:27:15,896 --> 01:27:19,161
This here's my wife Carmen. I call her Tootsie.

885
01:27:19,465 --> 01:27:21,899
That's our three-year-old daughter. Her name's Anna.

886
01:27:21,967 --> 01:27:24,902
That's my son Jim. He's 17, and he's my jackrabbit.

887
01:27:24,969 --> 01:27:26,970
-We need a room for three. -Three?

888
01:27:26,970 --> 01:27:29,495
-[Kitty Meows] -Oh, you got a cat. No problem.

889
01:27:29,905 --> 01:27:32,203
You need a room, you come to the right place.

890
01:27:32,306 --> 01:27:34,570
We got lots of rooms. Room 309.

891
01:27:34,608 --> 01:27:37,600
Hot out there, ain't it? It must be 114 degrees.

892
01:27:37,709 --> 01:27:40,576
Y'all come in for the races, I'll bet.

893
01:27:40,611 --> 01:27:43,307
Y-Y'all watch your step. Watch your step please, ma'am.

894
01:27:43,413 --> 01:27:46,314
A horse'll run a good second faster out there...

895
01:27:46,415 --> 01:27:48,315
than any other track in the country.

896
01:27:48,416 --> 01:27:50,111
It's just somethin'.

897
01:27:50,183 --> 01:27:52,818
Now, if one thing does hold true to form, it's the speed horse.

898
01:27:52,818 --> 01:27:56,879
A speed horse, he's runnin' just as hard as he can for as long as he can.

899
01:27:57,120 --> 01:28:01,580
What they try to do is to rate those things. That's a whole 'nother story.

900
01:28:01,623 --> 01:28:04,217
This here... This here's your livin' room.

901
01:28:04,325 --> 01:28:09,126
Bathroom, shower, toilet, bedroom, bed.

902
01:28:09,227 --> 01:28:11,627
Over in the top drawer you got the Gideon Bible.

903
01:28:11,696 --> 01:28:13,527
Right out here you got a veranda.

904
01:28:13,597 --> 01:28:15,531
Oh, it's just a beautiful sunset there, lady.

905
01:28:15,598 --> 01:28:18,226
Now... here you go.

906
01:28:18,333 --> 01:28:22,326
-What's in there? -That'd be your closet there. It's...

907
01:28:22,401 --> 01:28:26,132
Oh! God! What're ya... Oh!

908
01:28:26,237 --> 01:28:29,138
Open up your mouth. Say "Ahhh."

909
01:28:29,205 --> 01:28:31,435
Ahhh! Ahhh! [Groans]

910
01:28:31,540 --> 01:28:34,805
You got two choices here, pal: You can live or you can die.

911
01:28:34,842 --> 01:28:37,037
-What's it gonna be? -I don't wanna die.

912
01:28:37,143 --> 01:28:40,044
You do the right thing, you might even make a little bit of money.

913
01:28:40,145 --> 01:28:41,806
Huh?

914
01:29:00,123 --> 01:29:03,286
I'll tell you what. I'll go check us into the hotel.

915
01:29:03,392 --> 01:29:06,589
You go find someplace around here and get us some new clothes.

916
01:29:07,794 --> 01:29:11,355
Here you go, Doc. Passport.

917
01:29:11,397 --> 01:29:15,197
[Chuckles] Credit card, driver's license.

918
01:29:15,299 --> 01:29:18,097
All cherry stuff. Never been reported.

919
01:29:18,201 --> 01:29:20,396
That stuff's so good, you can go anywhere you want to,

920
01:29:20,469 --> 01:29:23,004
no matter how hot you may be.

921
01:29:23,004 --> 01:29:25,996
Here's the key to your room, 234.

922
01:29:26,305 --> 01:29:29,974
Nobody else on that floor but you. All you gotta do is lay low a while.

923
01:29:29,974 --> 01:29:32,909
Then we'll get you on out of here, okay?

924
01:29:33,109 --> 01:29:35,805
Carol went to get us some fresh clothes.

925
01:29:35,877 --> 01:29:38,573
We're both hungry. Send up some food as soon as you can.

926
01:29:38,612 --> 01:29:41,012
-How about some sandwiches? -That'll be fine.

927
01:29:41,080 --> 01:29:43,015
It's gonna be an hour, maybe more.

928
01:29:43,015 --> 01:29:46,507
When my wife comes back, have that kid take care of anything she might need.

929
01:29:46,884 --> 01:29:49,114
-I gave him the day off. -Then you do it.

930
01:29:49,219 --> 01:29:54,623
I can't. I-I've gotta watch the front desk. You know how it goes.

931
01:29:58,724 --> 01:30:03,093
Doc, look, I'll work on the food, okay? Doc!

932
01:30:03,127 --> 01:30:05,118
This ain't the Hilton.

933
01:30:25,639 --> 01:30:28,233
-Can I come in? -Sure.

934
01:30:41,049 --> 01:30:45,452
[Sighing]

935
01:32:11,067 --> 01:32:14,002
[Fran] Give me that room key, or I'll kill you...

936
01:32:14,068 --> 01:32:17,799
and I'll kill your little kitty too. [Chuckles]

937
01:32:17,871 --> 01:32:20,499
You see Gollie's face when he bounced off that door?

938
01:32:20,573 --> 01:32:23,064
[Lmitating Rudy] Hey, Gollie, what's in here?

939
01:32:23,108 --> 01:32:25,599
[Lmitating Gollie] I don't know. Let's find out.

940
01:32:25,676 --> 01:32:28,372
[Screams, Laughs]

941
01:32:28,410 --> 01:32:31,208
Open your mouth! Open it wider!

942
01:32:31,312 --> 01:32:34,304
[Telephone Rings]

943
01:32:39,984 --> 01:32:42,612
-Yeah? -[Gollie] He's here.

944
01:32:42,718 --> 01:32:45,278
Room 234.

945
01:32:45,320 --> 01:32:50,019
Wants me to bring him up some sandwiches in about an hour.

946
01:32:50,056 --> 01:32:52,251
Yeah, 234.

947
01:32:52,324 --> 01:32:54,349
Hang it up.

948
01:32:54,425 --> 01:32:58,054
-[Hangs Up Telephone] -Get dressed.

949
01:33:03,464 --> 01:33:06,433
-Good flight, Jim? -They still in there?

950
01:33:06,465 --> 01:33:10,629
Yeah, both of 'em. McCoy and his wife showed up a little while ago.

951
01:33:10,668 --> 01:33:12,966
Mm-hmm. That's nice.

952
01:33:13,070 --> 01:33:16,870
Fire up the grill, boys. It's barbecue time.

953
01:33:20,673 --> 01:33:23,767
-Want some of these? -Let's go, baby. Come on.

954
01:33:41,886 --> 01:33:44,787
Hey, wake up. Come on, let's go.

955
01:33:46,355 --> 01:33:48,482
What's the matter?

956
01:33:48,557 --> 01:33:52,789
Get dressed. We're leavin' right now.

957
01:33:52,893 --> 01:33:55,885
What is it?

958
01:33:55,994 --> 01:33:58,053
It's Gollie.

959
01:33:58,096 --> 01:34:01,190
Somethin' bothering me about him.

960
01:34:01,264 --> 01:34:03,562
He's always got his family around.

961
01:34:03,598 --> 01:34:06,066
That wife and kid of his always stick close...

962
01:34:06,100 --> 01:34:09,365
to make sure he stays away from the horses and the booze.

963
01:34:09,402 --> 01:34:11,461
So what?

964
01:34:11,503 --> 01:34:14,165
If they're not here, then there's somethin' wrong.

965
01:34:14,205 --> 01:34:16,173
Maybe they took the day off.

966
01:34:20,208 --> 01:34:22,802
What's the plan?

967
01:34:22,910 --> 01:34:25,606
The plan is, shut up.

968
01:34:41,720 --> 01:34:45,121
-Come on, baby, we gotta move. -[Knock At Door]

969
01:34:48,791 --> 01:34:50,725
Who is it?

970
01:34:50,792 --> 01:34:54,125
[Fran] Sandwiches for Mr. McCoy. It's your food, ma'am.

971
01:34:57,429 --> 01:35:01,991
He's in the shower. Can you leave them outside?

972
01:35:06,302 --> 01:35:09,203
Um, no, I can't do that, ma'am.

973
01:35:09,236 --> 01:35:12,738
You have to pay now, 'cause I have to pay the boy that brought up the food.

974
01:35:12,738 --> 01:35:16,105
Well, I'm not dressed. You'll have to wait.

975
01:35:17,942 --> 01:35:19,842
Hello?

976
01:35:21,109 --> 01:35:23,839
All right.

977
01:36:07,370 --> 01:36:10,862
[Fran] Ma'am, how much longer are you gonna be?

978
01:36:18,977 --> 01:36:21,571
-[Grunting] -[Fran Screaming] Rudy!

979
01:36:21,678 --> 01:36:25,876
My Rudy! Rudy! Don't touch my Rudy!

980
01:36:25,981 --> 01:36:28,415
Don't hurt my Rudy! Don't hurt my Rudy!

981
01:36:28,449 --> 01:36:31,043
Don't hurt my Rudy! [Grunts]

982
01:36:33,051 --> 01:36:35,019
[Grunts]

983
01:37:02,902 --> 01:37:05,427
[Releasing Hammer]

984
01:37:05,536 --> 01:37:08,130
Let's get out of here.

985
01:37:26,448 --> 01:37:30,043
-Ah, what is it? Is it... 204? -[Gollie Groaning]

986
01:37:30,118 --> 01:37:34,020
-Is it, uh, 314? -[Groaning Continues]

987
01:37:36,221 --> 01:37:38,155
Ooh!

988
01:37:38,222 --> 01:37:43,626
Ooh! My, my, my, my, my. Now, you may wanna watch this.

989
01:37:43,659 --> 01:37:46,958
What are you gonna do with that thing?

990
01:37:47,061 --> 01:37:51,225
-What are you doin' to me? No! No! -Right there.

991
01:37:53,064 --> 01:37:54,463
[Screaming]

